title: US federal agent shoots Chicago motorist as protests spread, while a judge blocks troops to Portland
byline: Le Monde with AP and AFP

title: The West Bank village of Palestine's forgotten Americans
subhed: In the occupied West Bank, 85% of Turmus Ayya's population are American-Palestinian citizens. Every summer, these dual nationals return to visit their families and maintain ties with their homeland. They find that their American passports offer no immunity from persecution by the army and settlers in this territory, where illegal Israeli settlements are rapidly expanding.

title: The dyeing marvels of 'magician' Serge Haouzi
subhed: Serge Haouzi is a master of color. In his studios in a southern Paris suburb, the director of Les Teintures de France and his team of colorists develop and enhance textile pieces for leading fashion houses. Their expertise relies on both artisanal processes and cutting-edge technology.

title: Former American diplomat Robert Malley: 'Trump's Gaza plan offers more ambiguities and potential pitfalls than clear answers'
subhed: In an interview with Le Monde, Robert Malley, who participated in peace negotiations between Israel and Palestine under Bill Clinton, Barack Obama and Joe Biden, sees Donald Trump's plan as yet another attempt that fails to take history into account. In particular, he questions the relevance of the two-state solution.
